Here are both approaches using `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel:

**1. Register the route in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:**

```csharp
public partial class AppShell : Shell
{
    public AppShell()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
    }
}
```

**2. Navigate from `ProductListPage` — two approaches:**

```csharp
// Approach A: Pass product ID as a query string
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B: Pass the full Product object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive data in the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`:**

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _productId;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Product _product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A: string parameter from query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service using the ID...
        }

        // Approach B: full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel to the page:**

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage
{
    public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | Query string (`?productId=...`) | `ShellNavigationQueryParameters` |
|---|---|---|
| **Data type** | Serialized as string | Any object, passed by reference |
| **Deep-link friendly** | ✅ Yes | ❌ No |
| **Complex objects** | ❌ Must fetch separately | ✅ Pass directly |

Always `await` `GoToAsync` calls to avoid race conditions. Use `ContentTemplate` with `DataTemplate` in your Shell XAML so pages load on demand.
